# Skill: Vanilla JS Rendering Components

Use this skill when editing `js/app.js` or static data files.

## Objective
Keep the app static and data-driven while making the renderer modular, safe, and maintainable.

## Core Rules
- Keep using vanilla JavaScript.
- Keep using `window.KHOBOR_DATA`.
- Keep the language state simple.
- Escape all dynamic text with `esc()` before rendering.
- Avoid adding dependencies.
- Avoid huge duplicated HTML blocks.

## Preferred Render Helpers
Create or maintain focused helpers such as:
- `renderIcon(name, className)`
- `renderSectionHeader(section)`
- `renderCategoryBadge(label)`
- `renderAuthorMeta(item)`
- `renderNewsCard(item, variant)`
- `renderFeatureCard(item)`
- `renderCompactCard(item)`
- `renderHorizontalCard(item)`
- `renderTrendingList(items)`
- `renderAdSlot(options)`
- `renderVideoCard(video)`
- `renderNewsletterBox(t)`
- `renderSearchOverlay(t)`
- `renderMobileMenu(t)`
- `renderBackToTopButton()`

## Data Rules
- Extend `base-data.js` only when required for UI sections.
- Keep Bangla and English data structures parallel.
- Keep dummy data clearly marked as dummy preview content.
- Do not hardcode large content directly inside render functions when it belongs in data.

## Interaction Rules
- Attach event listeners after rendering.
- Avoid attaching duplicate event listeners unintentionally.
- Keep overlay/menu state simple.
- Escape closes overlays.
- Keep alerts only for dummy behavior where no real backend exists.

## Acceptance Checklist
- Bangla/English toggle works after changes.
- Render helpers are readable and reusable.
- No console errors.
- Dynamic text is escaped.
- Code comments explain major render groups.
